wikipedia_page.main: George William Barnard (2 February 1804 – 1827) was an English first-class cricketer associated with Cambridge University who was active in the 1820s. He is recorded in two matches, 1825 to 1826, totalling 77 runs with a highest score of 50 and holding one catch.He was educated at Eton College and King's College, Cambridge; he died without taking his degree.
